full_text: Log in as an underwriter Alice Applegate. Find an account, for example, Ray Newton. Click the Contacts link in the sidebar. It opens the Account File Contacts page. Selecting a contact from the list refreshes the details at the bottom. Separate tabs display the contact detail, roles, addresses, associated transactions and policies. Contacts are identified by the role they fill. There are predefined account contact roles and policy contact roles. One contact can fill multiple roles on the account or policy. The contact Ray Newton has three account contact roles, Account Holder, Driver, and Named Insured. A contact role may have additional fields as for Driver. A contact can be edited by clicking the Edit button on the right. We will just cancel the edit without saving. To add a new contact on the account, click Create New Contact at the top. Select the desired contact role, for example, Additional Insured, and select either Person or Company. Enter required fields on the Contact Detail tab. The role of Additional Insured is added by default. Save the new contact. The list of contacts can be filtered by role. Select the Driver role. There are five contacts with the Driver role on the account. Go back to the Account Summary page. Open an Inforce policy. Open an Inforce policy. The contacts on a policy are listed under Policy Tools, Contacts. Ray Newton has two policy contact roles, Primary named Insured and Driver. The contacts on the account can be reused on the policies. Open a draft submission for Personal, Auto, or Create a new submission. Go to the Driver's screen. Click Add. Select Existing Driver. It lists the five contacts with a driver role from the account. Select John Smith. It is added to the submission. To create a new contact on the policy, click Add again. Select New Person. Enter required fields. Save the new policy driver. Go to the Roles tab. Enter additional information for the driver role, such as Year First Licensed. After clicking Save Draft in the submission, the new policy contact Mike Smith is added at the policy level. Go back to the account. Go to the Account Contacts page. Verify that the new policy contact Mike Smith is added to the account automatically. This is the end of contacts overview.
